SOWETO - Grace Bible Church in Soweto will be alive with song and dance on Tuesday as the public gathers to remember gospel artist Lundi Tyamara. The 38-year-old died after a long struggle with stomach TB and liver complications.Tyamara started his career as a backing vocalist for Rebecca Malope in the early 90's before launching a solo project under the guidance of Zuzmuzi Music founder Tshepo Nzimande.Some of his popular songs include:Ithemba lami likuweMphefumulo wamiNginga hlanzwa Ngithembu JesuAkuvumi The memorial service starts at 2pm.eNCA